long-description.p:
At The above location there are the remains of a stone windmill on a circular plinth.
The mill is only one of around 100 windmills known to have been worked in the then grain-rich county.
The mill is on private property there is no need to cross the open fields to the mill to find the cache
The cache is a small micro please rehide it well to prevent muggles from discovering its location
